node.text: Sam, Golden Retriever (16 y/o), Upper West Side, New York, NY • We’ve partnered with @thefarmersdog to tell the story of Sam, a senior rescue dog who’s living a long, fulfilling and healthy life. The Farmer’s Dog is helping senior dogs in shelters find homes in time for the holidays – follow the link at the end of the video to see adoptable seniors in shelters all across the country so hopefully you can find a Sam, too.

node.text: Team Dogist will be fostering Marble to help get him adopted from @SocialTeesNYC

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The Dogist on August 16, 2021 tagging @love4satos, and @thordoxiemix. May be an image of 1 person, dog and indoor.

node.text: Thor, Dachshund mix, Bala Cynwyd, PA • “He doesn’t like children or old people. He doesn’t trust them. Children have erratic movements. The teepee is his safe place. If he knows he’s about to get bathed he’ll be in his teepee. He has anxiety and takes puppy Prozac. Anything that’s stuffed will be de-stuffed in 25 minutes. We have a dog park below the window and he looks down at it every morning to check on his ‘constituents’.” @thordoxiemix, a rescue from @love4satos

node.text: Pingo, Whippet/Terrier mix (2 y/o), Chilmark, MA • “We love every part of her except when she sees wild animals and runs away. She sleeps completely under the covers – I have no idea how she breathes. That’s where she wants to be. She wants other dogs to chase her with the stick but not for them to get the stick. My parents didn’t want me to get her but she’s completely won their hearts. She’s somewhere between a cat and a seal.”
